# Discord User Account Configuration
# To enable Discord integration, copy this file to .env and fill in your values

# Your Discord user token (sends messages as YOUR account, not a bot)
# 
# WARNING: User token usage violates Discord's Terms of Service!
# Use at your own risk - Discord may ban your account if detected.
# For educational/personal use only.
#
# How to get your Discord user token:
# 1. Open Discord in your web browser (not the app)
# 2. Press F12 to open Developer Tools
# 3. Go to Network tab
# 4. Send any message in Discord
# 5. Look for a request to "messages" in the Network tab
# 6. Click on it, go to Headers, find "authorization" header
# 7. Copy the token (it's a long string of letters/numbers)
DISCORD_USER_TOKEN=your_user_token_here

# The Discord DM channel ID where encrypted messages will be sent
# 
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Enable Developer Mode in Discord (User Settings > Advanced > Developer Mode)
# 2. Start a DM conversation with the target user
# 3. Right-click on the DM conversation in your DM list, select "Copy ID"
# 4. Paste that ID below (it should start with numbers like 123456789...)
DISCORD_DM_ID=your_dm_channel_id_here

# Note: Messages will appear to come from YOUR Discord account